<subSubSection pageId="12" pageNumber="13" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1437,742,1542]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,340,858,884]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Discussion:</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Sokolow" box="[348,542,858,884]" pageId="12" pageNumber="33" refString="Sokolow, I. (1940) Hydracarina (1. re partie: Hydrachnellae). In: Sernow, A. &amp; Stackelberg, A. (eds.), Faune de l'URSS. Arachnides. Institute de l'Academie des Sciences de l'URSS, Moscow, Leningrad, pp. 1 - 511." type="book chapter" year="1940">
Sokolow (
<number box="[470,532,858,884]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" value="1940.0">1940</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
treated 
<taxonomicName box="[639,816,858,883]" class="Arachnida" family="Hydryphantidae" genus="Hydryphantes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="intermedius">
<emphasis box="[639,816,858,883]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">H. intermedius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as a 
<emphasis box="[879,1057,858,883]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
species 
<taxonomicName box="[973,1057,858,883]" class="Arachnida" family="Hydryphantidae" genus="Todothyas" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="incerta">incerta</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
– with good reasons in view of the rather sketchy figures given in the original description. However, the shape of the frontal shield (probably illustrated in an oblique position by Daday) is considered nowadays to be of minor importance, and other information available from the original description (frontal shield with long posterior extensions, high swimming hair numbers on legs, stout shape of palp) are in perfect agreement with 
<taxonomicName box="[1192,1309,1013,1038]" class="Arachnida" family="Hydryphantidae" genus="Hydryphantes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dispar">
<emphasis box="[1192,1309,1013,1038]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">H. dispar</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, a species obviously unknown to Daday. So, notwithstanding the loss of 
<typeStatus box="[906,958,1052,1078]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">type</typeStatus>
material, we consider 
<taxonomicName box="[1235,1414,1052,1077]" class="Arachnida" family="Hydryphantidae" genus="Hydryphantes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="intermedius">
<emphasis box="[1235,1414,1052,1077]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">H. intermedius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
a junior synonym of 
<taxonomicName box="[374,483,1091,1116]" class="Arachnida" family="Hydryphantidae" genus="Hydryphantes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dispar">
<emphasis box="[374,483,1091,1116]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">H. dispar</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1437,742,1542]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
In the description of 
<taxonomicName authority="Walter (1925)" authorityName="Walter" authorityYear="1925" box="[443,787,1129,1155]" class="Arachnida" family="Hydryphantidae" genus="Hydryphantes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="algeriensis">
<emphasis box="[443,608,1129,1154]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">H. algeriensis</emphasis>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Walter" box="[623,787,1129,1155]" pageId="12" pageNumber="34" refString="Walter, C. (1925) Hydracariens de l'Algerie et de la Tunisie (Collections de M. H. Gauthier), Premiere liste. Bulletin de la Societe d'Histoire Naturelle de l'Afrique du Nord, Alger, 16, 189 - 238." type="journal article" year="1925">
Walter (
<number box="[717,778,1129,1155]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" value="1925.0">1925</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
considered particularities in shape of the frontal shield and leg setation as diagnostic for 
<taxonomicName box="[544,709,1168,1193]" class="Arachnida" family="Hydryphantidae" genus="Hydryphantes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="algeriensis">
<emphasis box="[544,709,1168,1193]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">H. algeriensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. He considered the species as intermediate between 
<taxonomicName box="[1325,1436,1168,1193]" class="Arachnida" family="Hydryphantidae" genus="Hydryphantes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dispar">
<emphasis box="[1325,1436,1168,1193]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">H. dispar</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Koenike, 1915" authorityName="Koenike" authorityYear="1915" box="[203,579,1206,1232]" class="Arachnida" family="Hydryphantidae" genus="Hydryphantes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bucculentus">
<emphasis box="[203,387,1207,1232]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">H. bucculentus</emphasis>
Koenike, 
<number box="[515,579,1206,1232]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" value="1915.0">1915</number>
</taxonomicName>
, synonymized with 
<taxonomicName box="[825,941,1207,1232]" class="Arachnida" family="Hydryphantidae" genus="Hydryphantes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dispar">
<emphasis box="[825,941,1207,1232]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">H. dispar</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Viets" box="[989,1183,1206,1232]" pageId="12" pageNumber="33" refString="Viets, K. (1956) Die Milben des Sußwassers und des Meeres. Hydrachnellae et Halacaridae (Acari). II. und III. Teil: Katalog und Nomenklator. G. Fischer, Jena, 870 pp." type="book" year="1956">
K. Viets (
<number box="[1107,1174,1206,1232]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" value="1956.0">1956</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
. In the 
<typeStatus box="[1276,1386,1206,1232]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">holotype</typeStatus>
, the following details and measurements were observed: Frontal shield total L/medial L/W 
